modules.description: This module provides direct access to UTF-8 encoded Unicode emoji strings, covering a comprehensive range of categories including facial expressions, human figures with skin tone variations, animals, objects, symbols, and composite emojis using zero-width joiners. It exposes individual emoji values and categorized arrays (e.g., subcategories like "gestures" or "zodiac signs") for structured access, enabling use cases such as building inclusive user interfaces, enriching text-based communication, or implementing emoji-based data visualization. The design emphasizes explicit naming and modifier combinations (e.g., skin tones, gender pairings) to support accessibility and cultural representation in applications.
